1 packet salmon
1 packet Sichuan garlic paste
1 pear
1 cucumber
1 bag Slaw Mix
1 packet mayonnaise
1 packet Japanese Dressing
1 packet Microwavable Basmati Rice
1 bag coriander
olive oil

• Pat salmon dry with paper towel and season.
• Heat olive oil in a frying pan over medium-high heat.
• Cook salmon, skin-side down first, until just cooked through, 3-4 mins each side.
• Remove pan from heat, add Sichuan paste and turn to coat.

• Slice pear and cucumber into thin sticks.
• In a bowl, combine slaw mix, pear and cucumber.
• Add mayo and Japanese dressing, toss and season to taste.

• Microwave rice until steaming, 2-3 mins.
• Plate up rice, salmon and slaw.
• Serve topped with torn coriander.